> [!WARNING]
> This is a large, interconnected refactor touching every crate in the workspace. The changes must be applied in dependency order (core-types first, then ring-buffer/seqlock, then order-book, then matching-engine, etc.) to avoid intermediate broken states.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Open question**: The project has TWO different type hierarchies — the "architecture doc" style (`InboundCommand`, `SequencedCommand`, `EngineEvent`, `Symbol`) and the "gateway/session" style (`Command`, `Event`, `InstrumentId`). Should we:
> 1. **(Recommended)** Keep BOTH — `Command`/`Event` for the gateway wire protocol layer, `InboundCommand`/`SequencedCommand`/`EngineEvent` for the engine-internal path, with conversions between them
> 2. Merge them into a single unified type hierarchy (simpler but loses the separation)
>
> I recommend option 1 since the gateway needs its own clean wire-protocol types distinct from the engine-internal sequenced types.

